        {
          "anchor" : "Comparator",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Comparator",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Compares two voltages and outputs a digital signal based on the comparison",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "columns" : [
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "identifier" : "Example_Comparator",
                      "type" : "image"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ],
              "size" : 1
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "identifier" : "Diagram_Comparator",
                      "type" : "image"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ],
              "size" : 1
            }
          ],
          "numberOfColumns" : 2,
          "type" : "row"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "The comparator has five pins:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "items" : [
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "inlineContent" : [
                        {
                          "text" : "Power",
                          "type" : "text"
                        }
                      ],
                      "type" : "strong"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " (pin 8): 5 Volts, for example",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "inlineContent" : [
                        {
                          "text" : "Ground",
                          "type" : "text"
                        }
                      ],
                      "type" : "strong"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " (pin 1 and 4): 0 Volts. May also be negative sometimes? But not usually.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "inlineContent" : [
                        {
                          "text" : "V1",
                          "type" : "text"
                        }
                      ],
                      "type" : "strong"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " aka ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "inlineContent" : [
                        {
                          "text" : "Vref",
                          "type" : "text"
                        }
                      ],
                      "type" : "strong"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " aka ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "inlineContent" : [
                        {
                          "text" : "Vin+",
                          "type" : "text"
                        }
                      ],
                      "type" : "strong"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " aka ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "inlineContent" : [
                        {
                          "text" : "V+",
                          "type" : "text"
                        }
                      ],
                      "type" : "strong"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " (pin 2): Reference voltage, the voltage to compare against",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "inlineContent" : [
                        {
                          "text" : "V2",
                          "type" : "text"
                        }
                      ],
                      "type" : "strong"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " aka ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "inlineContent" : [
                        {
                          "text" : "Vin",
                          "type" : "text"
                        }
                      ],
                      "type" : "strong"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " aka ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "inlineContent" : [
                        {
                          "text" : "Vin-",
                          "type" : "text"
                        }
                      ],
                      "type" : "strong"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " aka ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "inlineContent" : [
                        {
                          "text" : "V-",
                          "type" : "text"
                        }
                      ],
                      "type" : "strong"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " (pin 3): Input voltage, the voltage to compare",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "inlineContent" : [
                        {
                          "text" : "Output",
                          "type" : "text"
                        }
                      ],
                      "type" : "strong"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " aka ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "inlineContent" : [
                        {
                          "text" : "Vout",
                          "type" : "text"
                        }
                      ],
                      "type" : "strong"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " (pin 7): Digital output, high or low. High if V2 > V1, low otherwise.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "type" : "unorderedList"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Note that there are two other pins 5 and 6. Just connect them together and forget about it, because its out of",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "syllabus.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Use a voltage divider (see ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "doc:\/\/Notes\/documentation\/Notes\/Circuit-Theories",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : ") for Vref to fix it at a certain voltage. Usually, you only",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "need to vary V2, by connecting it to a potentiometer or thermistor some other variable voltage source.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Note that voltage comparators operate on ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "inlineContent" : [
                {
                  "text" : "open collector",
                  "type" : "text"
                }
              ],
              "type" : "strong"
            },
            {
              "text" : ", meaning that the output can’t be considered simply",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "“high” or “low”. When it is “low”, it acts as normal and connects to ground. However, when it is “high”, it",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "disconnects from the circuit entirely. You need to ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "inlineContent" : [
                {
                  "text" : "connect a pull-up resistor",
                  "type" : "text"
                }
              ],
              "type" : "strong"
            },
            {
              "text" : " to the output to ensure that it",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "is “high” when the comparator is not outputting a signal.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "In the arrangement as seen in the image, if you imagine an LED at R, an OFF (0V) would turn it on, and an ON (floating)",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "would turn it off, because the Vout acts as ground for the LED. If you need the opposite behaviour, use a transistor",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "(see ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "doc:\/\/Notes\/documentation\/Notes\/Bipolar-Junction-Transistors",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : ") to invert the signal.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Timer",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Timer",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Has two modes: monostable and astable. They’re very different so they’re explained separately.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "The 555 timer IC is a common timer IC. It has 8 pins:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "items" : [
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "inlineContent" : [
                        {
                          "text" : "Power",
                          "type" : "text"
                        }
                      ],
                      "type" : "strong"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " (pin 8): 5 Volts, for example",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "inlineContent" : [
                        {
                          "text" : "Ground",
                          "type" : "text"
                        }
                      ],
                      "type" : "strong"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " (pin 1): 0 Volts",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "inlineContent" : [
                        {
                          "text" : "Trigger",
                          "type" : "text"
                        }
                      ],
                      "type" : "strong"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " (pin 2): Input to trigger the timer",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "inlineContent" : [
                        {
                          "text" : "Output",
                          "type" : "text"
                        }
                      ],
                      "type" : "strong"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " (pin 3): Output of the timer",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "inlineContent" : [
                        {
                          "text" : "Reset",
                          "type" : "text"
                        }
                      ],
                      "type" : "strong"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " (pin 4): Reset the timer",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "inlineContent" : [
                        {
                          "text" : "Control Voltage",
                          "type" : "text"
                        }
                      ],
                      "type" : "strong"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " (pin 5): Not used, connect to ground. Optionally connect a filtering capacitor.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "inlineContent" : [
                        {
                          "text" : "Threshold",
                          "type" : "text"
                        }
                      ],
                      "type" : "strong"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " (pin 6): Threshold voltage",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "inlineContent" : [
                        {
                          "text" : "Discharge",
                          "type" : "text"
                        }
                      ],
                      "type" : "strong"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " (pin 7): Discharge pin",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "type" : "unorderedList"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Monostable",
          "level" : 3,
          "text" : "Monostable",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Outputs a pulse of a fixed duration when triggered.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "identifier" : "Diagram_Monostable_Timer",
              "type" : "image"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "The timer has two resistors and a capacitor connected to it. The duration of the pulse is given by the formula:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "T = 1.1 * R1 * C1"
          ],
          "syntax" : "math",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "where",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "items" : [
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "code" : "T",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " is the duration of the pulse,",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "code" : "R1",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " is the resistance of the resistor connected to the timer, and",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "code" : "C1",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " is the capacitance of the capacitor connected to the timer. This formula is given in the test paper.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "type" : "unorderedList"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "The timer is triggered by a low signal on the trigger pin. The output pin goes high for the duration of the pulse, then goes low.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Process:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "items" : [
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "The trigger pin drops from high (above 2\/3 Vcc) to a low (below 1\/3 Vcc).",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "IC connects pin 7 (discharge) to ground, immediately discharging the capacitor.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "The output pin goes high.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "The capacitor charges up. The speed of charging is inversely related to the resistance and capacitance.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "The capacitor is charged to 2\/3 Vcc. It is detected by pin 6 (threshold).",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Output pin goes low",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Capacitor discharges immediately, ready for the next trigger.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "type" : "orderedList"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Astable",
          "level" : 3,
          "text" : "Astable",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Outputs a continuous stream of pulses",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "identifier" : "Diagram_Astable_Timer",
              "type" : "image"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "The timer has two resistors and a capacitor connected to it. The frequency of the pulses is given by the formula:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "T = \\frac{(R_1 + 2R_2) * C_1}{1.44}",
            "",
            "T_{on} = 0.693 * R_2 * C_1",
            "",
            "T_{off} = 0.693 * (R_1 + R_2) * C_1"
          ],
          "syntax" : "math",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Where",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "items" : [
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "code" : "T",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " is the period of the pulse,",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "code" : "T_on",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " is the duration of the high state,",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "code" : "T_off",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " is the duration of the low state,",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "code" : "R1",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " is the resistance of the resistor connected to the timer, and",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "code" : "C1",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " is the capacitance of the capacitor connected to the timer. This formula is given in the test paper.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "type" : "unorderedList"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "The timer outputs a continuous stream of pulses. The output pin goes high for a certain duration, then goes low for a certain",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "duration. The duration of the high and low states is determined by the resistors and capacitor connected to the timer.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Process:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "items" : [
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "The capacitor charges up through R1 and R2. The speed of charging is inversely related to the resistance and capacitance.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "The capacitor is charged to 2\/3 Vcc. It is detected by pin 6 (threshold).",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
